               manslaughter
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190526-42-person436">
                  WILLIAM 
                  COX
               <interp inst="t18190526-42-person436" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person436" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person436" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a gardener, and live at Hadley. On the 9th of March I was on Hadley-common, and saw three chaises coming along, one drove faster than the others, and as it passed the other two it made the horse turn short off, and one of the chaises, drove over a 
               <persName id="t18190526-42-victim437" type="victimName">
                     <rs id="t18190526-42-viclabel231" type="occupation">child</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190526-42-victim437 t18190526-42-viclabel231"></join>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-victim437" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190526-42-off230 t18190526-42-victim437"></join>
                  </persName>
             - the prisoner drove one of the chaises, but not that that occasioned the accident - it was an accident, and nothing else.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190526-42-person438">
                  MATTHEW 
                  COX
               <interp inst="t18190526-42-person438" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person438" type="given" value="MATTHEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person438" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw this accident. Two chaises were driving at a steady pace, another, which the prisoner drove, passed them, one of the horses took fright, and ran over the child, which was killed on the spot.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190526-42-person439">
                  PHILLIP 
                  EDRIDGE
               <interp inst="t18190526-42-person439" type="surname" value="EDRIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person439" type="given" value="PHILLIP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190526-42-person439" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was present. It was nothing but an accident.</p>
